              Thanks, Hat.  I'll bookmark this for when I help a friend upgrade his Win2K machine.<BR><BR>In WinXP, it should be noted that you can just use a Repair Install.  You'll have to reinstall all your drivers, though, but at least your apps will be intact, and the procedure is easy to remember.  (Boot from XP CD, skip the first repair option, choose Repair Install.)

              

              
              
