              yeah, we were pretty lucky. Pulled a p2L97 (i440fx pentium 2) with a p2 300 on it, and swapped in some ECS with a duron 1.2 <BR><BR>WinXP pro, worked flawlessly. boot --&gt; detect new hardware --&gt; install --&gt; reboot.<BR><BR>Of course, being lazy was ok, because it was an HTPC and the only drive that would need reinstalling (if a repair was needed) was detonators. <BR><BR>heh.<BR><BR>For 2k though, my hat is off to you... hat. heh. Has anyone tried that with NT4? just curious. hehe

              

              
              
